# Normalize line endings so a Windows checkout under the default core.autocrlf=true
# does not rewrite the checked-in generated files to CRLF: the sourcegen drift gate
# (crates/squonk-sourcegen, generated_files_are_up_to_date) compares on-disk bytes
# against fresh LF-emitting generation, and CRLF in the working tree would fail it
# spuriously. See the "Windows" section of docs/platform-support.md.
#
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect binary content and leave it untouched (the tree
# currently carries no binary files); `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree on every
# platform. The `\r\n` byte sequences some Rust tests rely on are source-level escape
# sequences ("\r\n"), not real CR bytes on disk, so newline normalization never
# perturbs them.
* text=auto eol=lf
